      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I was told,and have even read about it on these boards at some point,that Total Domination was disabled in a nerf to tone down enchanters ability to charm.Is there a way to find out if this is in fact true? If so can we push to have it reinstated or for a refund to the AA's spent on the ability?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As for the charisma issue,if charisma does indeed have a significant impact on mezz and charm,then why not push for an overcap to charisma with our charisma buffs?I believe Overwhelming Slendour was our last at lvl 56 with a 50 point boost - why not make a lvl 60+ version(say 65) with a +75 to charisma,50 point overcap? This brings us to a max of 415 on charisma at the expense of a spell slot,and this is also considering the enchanter is maxed on charisma to begin with.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a side note,I have seen several referances to possible augmentations that may be used to help boost our mezz,charm,stun,effectiveness,by increasing their duration,lowering recast times,lowering mana consumption,whatever - and something I believe needs be added to this is the ability to have these augs able to be placed in either &amp;quot;any&amp;quot; slot or the type 4 normally used for weapon procs.I managed to get my 2.0 today,and was at a loss as to what I should place in the type 4 slot,and although I recieved several ideas from fellow guildies,they almost all revolved around semi weak hp/mana augs that didnt provide any significant boost to the item.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Melee have an enourmous variety of augs to choose from that are all placed in slot 4,yet casters have to actually rely on those very same augs unless they have completed a quest such as the BiC aug.Casters dont survive long in combat on mobs that hit for 4k - so its kinda silly for our primaries to have weapon procs unless we depend on that item to solo weak mobs with.Focus effect augs,augs that provide a boost to hp/mana,augs that provide regen abilities,are the types of augs we need for our slot 4,or &amp;quot;any&amp;quot; slot such as the BiC.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
