      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm not really having issues with mez so much anymore, altho I still feel that mezzes should be softcapped. I've completed my DoD spell arcs and a few other missions, most on hard, and have rather few mez resists, and even on those resists I survive more often than not now between dodging, Boggle, and Rune of Shadows. If, early in a mission, I notice issues with mez resists, I pull out Greater Fetter to improve my chances of keeping things under control. My 66 pet also serves regularly to offtank just long enough to give me a moment more time to get things in check or pull an add off of another caster (I keep him up and only use him to OT with in a problem pull, which will usually involve root anyways, otherwise he's dps and buffers will often buff him. Pet Affinity goes a long way in this). My only major issue with all of it has been that I'm still riding Forlorn... I could really use Desolate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I have noticed, though, that I get mobs sometimes who are fairly easy to mez, but resist MR nukes and cripple. I sometimes think something has changed on the back end to make mezzing... specifically... a little easier in recent content, but not a global reduction in MR.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mind buffs after KEI should overcap INT/WIS. I'd like to see them include a spell haste component too, or perhaps some spell haste in an aura, but that's just me. Our nukes need to be just a tad more competitive, and/or our dots need to be made at all competitive. Hooray for increased mana regen, I hardly ever even use charm anymore so whatever happens happens (and if it goes well I'll be happy about it), and we won't get FM so I still propose Advanced Spellcasting Subtlety for less aggro on all our spells.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;But, while we still need work, I think some people have an issue with wanting to keep a single line of spells up all or most of the time. I've had to learn to be versatile again, and I do pretty well. My next step is to max Enhanced Forgetfulness and see if I can use memblur effectively during CC to further improve my survivability. I already mez, slow, debuff, nuke, buff, root, Mana Flare, NDT, and manage my pet, all as the situation calls for, with a comfortable degree of success... I honestly have less to complain about as far as versatility in groups than I used to. It just takes practice and patience. Raids, however, I cannot speak for at all since I almost never raid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
